** Felix Sasaki (DFKI / W3C Fellow):  [[Media:Lider-workshop-20140509-panel4-sasaki.pdf| statement]]
* '''12:00 - 12:30''' '''Requirements gathering''' about language resources data/metadata transformation and use cases discussion
* '''12:30 - 12:45''' Wrap-up

The event is supported by the [http://lider-project.eu/ LIDER EU project], the [http://www.multilingualweb.eu/ MultilingualWeb community], the [http://nlp2rdf.org NLP2RDF] project, the [http://linguistics.okfn.org/ Working Group for Open Data in Linguistics] as well as the [http://dbpedia.org DBpedia Project]. 

As input to the discussion and the work of the LD4LT group, we invite you to take a few short minutes to fill in the [https://www.w3.org/2002/09/wbs/1/ld4lt-wbs1/ first LIDER '''survey''']. During the meeting, via the survey and through the LD4LT group, you will have the opportunity to offer your view on how linked data and language technology should benefit each other.

== Registration == 
Participation is '''free'''. Please register for the event [https://www.w3.org/2002/09/wbs/1/lider-rmws-20140508-09/ here]. For the 9 May morning session we welcome '''position statements''' related to the topic of language resource RDF conversion. If you are interested in contributing a position statement please indicate this in the dedicated field in the registration form. The workshop organizers will come back to you with questions to answer in the position statement. We then will select statements and inform you by 28 April.

